{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-10-01-how-to-change-icon-size-in-react-js/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To change icon size in react js, you can use . It will change icon size in react js. Today, I am going to show you, how to‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To change icon size in react js, you can use <code class=\"language-text\">style={{fontSize:'50px'}}</code>. It will change icon size in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to change icon size in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h2>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h2>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Install a Font Icon Library</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @fortawesome<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>fontawesome @fortawesome<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>free<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>solid<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>svg<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>icons</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 2: Import react component.</h2>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> FontAwesomeIcon <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@fortawesome/react-fontawesome'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> faCoffee <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@fortawesome/free-solid-svg-icons'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 3: Create a Component.</h2>\n<p>You can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;FontAwesomeIcon icon={faCoffee} style={{fontSize:'50px'}} /></code> to change icon size in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>FontAwesomeIcon icon<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>faCoffee<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>FontAwesomeIcon icon<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>faCoffee<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> style<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token literal-property property\">fontSize</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token string\">'50px'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Change icon size example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">@fortawesome/react-fontawesome'</code> and use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;FontAwesomeIcon icon={faCoffee} style={{fontSize:'50px'}} /></code> to change icon size in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> FontAwesomeIcon <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@fortawesome/react-fontawesome'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> faCoffee <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@fortawesome/free-solid-svg-icons'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">App</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>FontAwesomeIcon icon<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>faCoffee<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>FontAwesomeIcon icon<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>faCoffee<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> style<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token literal-property property\">fontSize</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token string\">'50px'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">style={{fontSize:'50px'}}</code> to change icon size in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 321px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7c08dab186e47e6684e0c09532c59bba/2525c/icon-size.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 68.35443037974683%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; backg